  <p>The exercise stress test, or ergometry, is a key examination for evaluating your heart's response to physical exertion.</p>

  <p>The clinic performs this examination on a stationary bicycle while recording the electrocardiogram (ECG) in real time. The test identifies potential coronary artery disease through ECG changes during physical exertion that reveal possible arterial narrowing.</p>

  <p>Beyond cardiovascular screening, the stress test provides a comprehensive evaluation of fatigue, blood pressure and pulse evolution, and rhythm disorder monitoring.</p>
